        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Enon, or 7 miles southeast of East Bend, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Yadkinville...
East Bend...
Courtney...
Huntsville...
Shacktown...
Enon...
and Lone Hickory.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
